headline: When Christmas and Hanukkah Collide, Beware of Fire Hazards
summary: Rarely do Christmas and Hanukkah start on the same day, a phenomenon colloquially known as Chrismukkah.  “It’s nice to get it all done the same day,” said Marin Christensen of Duluth, Minn., a 33-year-old insurance-industry professional who took up Judaism about four years ago.  Christmas and Hanukkah seldom overlap.
